<div class="container">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
			<p class="company-description">
				Appcelerator has two main products: an enterprise MBaaS solution serving over 70% of the Fortune 100 called the Appcelerator Platform and a Javascript to native code compiler called Titanium with an open source developer community of 780,000.
			</p>
			<p>
				I joined the Appcelerator team during the exciting <%= link_to "Singly acquisition", "http://venturebeat.com/2013/08/22/why-did-appcelerator-buy-singly-because-it-wants-to-be-the-next-oracle/", target: "_blank" %>. During that time, Appcelerator was focused on selling an enterprise platform consisting of three products: <em>Apps</em>, <em>Analytics</em>, and <em>APIs</em>. My new director was interested in bringing life into the company, so I, heavily influenced by Parse and Urban Airship, spent a healthy amount of time redefining the brand which ultimately resulted in the trifecta emblem for the platform.
			</p>
			<div class="group-vertical-margin">
				<%= image_tag 'appcelerator/appc-header-platform.jpg', class: "img-responsive work group-vertical-margin" %>
			</div>
			<p>
				The enblem stood for each pillar of the platform. Below is an example of the website that encompasses the new brand direction I developed.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
